column6: Modern-Chic APT. Wolseley charm. Stylish getaway!
column7:
Welcome to the fully independent 1st floor apt of our character house! Refined and chic cocoon for a unique experience in the heart of our historic Wolseley neighborhood.

The apartment has been completely renovated and decorated in a chic and refined inspiration reminiscent of contemporary European glamour interiors!

We have thought of all the details worthy of a luxury hotel to make your getaway unforgettable!

It's not just a rental... It's your adventure and it should be flawless!
column8:
Wolseley is an incredibly diverse neighbourhood where the cool kids, families, artsy types, and all round good people call home. It’s affectionately known as “The Granola Belt?of Winnipeg and it features one of the most intact pre-1930 residential areas in Canada. It’s pretty much the poster child of whimsical charm in Winnipeg.

The Wolseley is overlooked as a residential area with a bohemian reputation and pedestrian-only summer roads. This neighbourhood’s beautiful old houses, charming cafes and artistic alleyways make it a must-see!
column15:
Welcome to our home! Welcome to your next adventure!

We are a couple from Europe living in Winnipeg for 7 years (Irene) and 25 years (Dario).
We are passionate about art, culture, architecture, design, travel and Beauty in all its expressions!
With European artistic influences, we have created this unique place to make your getaway unforgettable. In addition to our hospitality and attention to detail, we take advantage of Irene's decades of experience in tourism and our sparkling personalities, just like our product!
We look forward to meeting you and providing you with a flawless experience!

We love to travel and when we do, we want nothing less than authenticity, to experience the local life and to get the best out of every experience! It is with this same perspective that we take pride in creating great experiences for our guests!

Together we speak 7 languages: French, English, Spanish, Russian, Italian (a bit), Serbian and Croatian!

column8:
Winnipeg, Manitoba, Canada
Located in southwest Winnipeg, Bridgewater/ Praire Pointe is sure to impress! This vibrant community is full of natural beauty, as well as being equipped with a convenient Village Centre which includes shopping, banks, restaurants and a fitness centre - You'll have everything you need!

The location of this community is just one of its awesome features. Being on the edge of the city provides easy access to the perimeter, but is also close in proximity to all of your shopping needs. With 5 minute walking distance to the transit bus stop, close to University of Manitoba and easy access to downtown.

With an abundance of parks and hiking trails this community provides many options for the active family! Whether that is walking along the 9 kilometres of walking and cycling trails, or watching the wildlife in the teeming native grasses and wetlands, you'll always have something to do!

column6: Tree House "Tupper House" Heritage Experience
column7:
You won’t forget your stay in this romantic, memorable home. This 1800's mansion has been restored with elegant amenities for quite, romantic relaxation and enjoyment. Nestled in quite river bend of Winnipeg's only designated Historic neighbourhood, you will find yourself with village vibes yet centrally located/walking distance to all of Winnipeg's best! (Downtown, Corydon, Osborn, South Sherbrook strip). If your comfortable with stairs do not miss this chance.

The space
Vaulted ceilings create very unique cozy rooms. Each room has new high quality memory foam mattress's (Queen bed), separate Heating, and individual A/C unit to control your own temps. Floor includes Kitchenette, Large relax bathroom with soaker tub, communal lounging and dinning space with two rooms. Below is a full kitchen and 2nd bathroom with shower.
column8:
Very secluded and private designated historic neighbourhood very safe community with neighbourhood watch. Everyone knows each other around here with next to no traffic! Silent at night except for the rain drops.
Only three streets inside the river bend referred to as "The Gates" East Gate, Middle Gate, West Gate" has three historic gated entries however the gates are left open these days. Countless movie productions have been made within "The Gates" community and is a regular occurrence. Glimpses of the house can be seen in Home Alone 5 and the adjacent house was featured on the Home Alone 5 cover. History abounds as you view the Mansions of the merchants where such prestigious families live and have lived. This home was lived in by the Son of a Father of Confederation, and the King's Council. Across the street once belonged the the founders of the Hudson Bay Company.

column25:
You will be staying in Bridgewater, a new development near route 90 and the Tuxedo border. Central to many things, yet private in its location. This neighborhood is known for its friendly community and desirable, safe central location. I'd venture to say, it's one of if not the most affluent neighborhoods in the city. It's definitely one of my favorites.

The outlet mall is new this year and within a 2 minute drive. Right next to the new mall is IKEA. Both are well worth checking out!

For breakfast, Stella's is less than a few minutes away, just north up Kenaston - one of my favorite spots.

Head further north approximately 5 minutes, and you are now nearing the St. James area and Polo Park which has arguably the best shopping in the city.

Head east and follow Route 90 north to Corydon, then head east - you are at confusion corner, and in a total of fifteen minutes you will find yourself in the heart of Winnipeg's Little Italy / Osborne Village

column6: Quaint “Tupper House" Heritage Experience
column7:
You won’t forget your stay in this romantic, memorable home. This 1800's mansion has been restored with elegant amenities for quite, romantic relaxation and enjoyment. Nestled in quite river bend of Winnipeg's only designated Historic neighbourhood, you will find yourself with village vibes yet centrally located/walking distance to all of Winnipeg's best! (Downtown, Corydon, Osborn, South Sherbrook strip). If your comfortable with stairs do not miss this chance.

The space
Vaulted ceilings create very unique cozy rooms. Each room has new high quality memory foam mattress's (Queen Bed), separate Heating, and individual A/C unit to control your own temps. Floor includes Kitchenette, Large relax bathroom with soaker tub, communal lounging and dinning space with two rooms. Below is a full kitchen and 2nd bathroom with shower.
column8:
Very secluded and private designated historic neighbourhood very safe community with neighbourhood watch. Everyone knows each other around here with next to no traffic! Silent at night except for the rain drops.
Only three streets inside the river bend referred to as "The Gates" East Gate, Middle Gate, West Gate has three historic gated entries however the gates are left open these days. Countless movie productions have been made within "The Gates" community and is a regular occurrence. Glimpses of the house can be seen in Home Alone 5 and the adjacent house was featured on the Home Alone 5 cover. History abounds as you view the Mansions of the merchants where such prestigious families live and have lived. This home was lived in by the Son of a Father of Confederation, and the King's Council. Across the street once belonged the the founders of the Hudson Bay Company.

column15: Hello, my name is Lorraine and I live in the beautiful city of Winnipeg in the province of Manitoba which is located in the amazing country called Canada. I currently work in real estate, this is a new area for me and prior to that I was a support worker who cared for people living with disabilities. I love to host and was a host on Airbnb many years ago. I really enjoyed having guests come to my home and making them feel at home in my home. I hope one day you will be one of my guests and allow me to tell you about the many positives about the city of Winnipeg, such as the connection to Winnie the pooh and how we were chosen to have the museum of human rights and how we were the first city in the world to develop the 911 emergency number.

Hi! I’m Ajibola. My husband and I love hosting people. He's a Senior IT Project Manager and I’m a Senior HR Generalist. We are thrilled to welcome  guests from around the world to our luxurious, cozy and spacious space. It’s just the kind of place that we would want to stay if we were visiting Winnipeg, Manitoba! 

We enjoy meeting interesting, creative and passionate people from near and far and sharing our Winnipeg and Manitoba experience with them- the history, food, art, architecture and music. We are relaxed and welcoming. Staying with us is like staying with friends or family.

We always endeavor to make each guest’s stay wonderfully memorable.
During your stay, guest interaction can be tailored to your needs. My goal is to make your stay interesting and unforgettable.

During your stay

We live upstairs and there is keypad for self check in through the side door. We are available to assist in any way we can, and can interact in person (while maintaining COVID-19 guidelines), through text messages or Airbnb platform. We will be as interactive as you want.

column15:
My story 

As a child, I watched my mother host hundreds of visitors from all around the world. I would wonder why she would invite all these people at home for dinner, lunch or breakfast. Sometimes some would stay for a week, a month or just a few days.  My mother would go the extra mile to make sure all the guests felt at home. She was and still is the most wonderful host I ever known.

Now that I have grown, I understand that this is a natural gift that she had and took pride in. She found, still finds great satisfaction in it.

I started to join my mother in this beautiful adventure, and I started to fall in love with hosting guests with her. And now, it’s always a joy to host friends at my own house.

My siblings say that I love to serve people. And that can’t be far from the truth. 

I started thinking of being an Airbnb host since 2017. I even opened an account but as they say, God’s time is always the best. Last year , we decided to go all in with my husband.

For the few months, this has been the best adventure we both are on. So great to host incredible people who are visiting our beautiful city of Winnipeg. 

And as someone who travels and uses Airbnb in other cities, I knew exactly what guests love. We’ve made sure that when you stay at any of our properties, it’s a home away from home experience. 

We’ve gone above & beyond to make sure that when you book your stay with us, you’ll have the most memorable time. And you’ll have everything you need. 

So if you have friends or family visiting Winnipeg and they would love a place to stay, we would be happy to host them. 

We currently have 3 Short Term Rentals. And we are Now SUPERHOST .  View them and watch the virtual tour for the 2 of them.

I’m really excited to host you & your families.

If you love nice patios and al fresco dining, gelato, and an all round jovial atmosphere, then Corydon Avenue is for you. Once known as Winnipeg’s “Little Italy,?Corydon Ave is a destination district, one which is popular with visitors and locals alike for people watching, shopping and dining.

A vast array of cuisines are available ?from Japanese ramen, to Korean BBQ, to locally-sourced burgers, to sushi ?while classic Italiano institutions serving gelati and strong shots of espresso are evident throughout. It’s also still the neighbourhood to go watch Italy play, should the World Cup or Euros be on.

Corydon is also quite the shopping destination as trés chic shops now populate the avenue featuring everything from on-trend clothing stores to jewellery, while it has also become a popular salon and nail bar spot.

The area’s vibe is certainly artsy, as was recently emphasized Corydon Avenue Biz’s “street scaping.?The Colours of Corydon features eight h

column15:
My story 

As a child, I watched my mother host hundreds of visitors from all around the world. I would wonder why she would invite all these people at home for dinner, lunch or breakfast. Sometimes some would stay for a week, a month or just a few days.  My mother would go the extra mile to make sure all the guests felt at home. She was and still is the most wonderful host I ever known.

Now that I have grown, I understand that this is a natural gift that she had and took pride in. She found, still finds great satisfaction in it.

I started to join my mother in this beautiful adventure, and I started to fall in love with hosting guests with her. And now, it’s always a joy to host friends at my own house.

My siblings say that I love to serve people. And that can’t be far from the truth. 

I started thinking of being an Airbnb host since 2017. I even opened an account but as they say, God’s time is always the best. Last year , we decided to go all in with my husband.

For the few months, this has been the best adventure we both are on. So great to host incredible people who are visiting our beautiful city of Winnipeg. 

And as someone who travels and uses Airbnb in other cities, I knew exactly what guests love. We’ve made sure that when you stay at any of our properties, it’s a home away from home experience. 

We’ve gone above & beyond to make sure that when you book your stay with us, you’ll have the most memorable time. And you’ll have everything you need. 

So if you have friends or family visiting Winnipeg and they would love a place to stay, we would be happy to host them. 

We currently have 3 Short Term Rentals. And we are Now SUPERHOST .  View them and watch the virtual tour for the 2 of them.

I’m really excited to host you & your families.

column8:
You will be in a quiet yet dynamic residential neighbourhood which is considered a bit of a "hidden gem".

The Scotia Heights neighbourhood is east of Main Street and runs from Saint Johns Park to Kildonan Park. Scotia Street, which is 5 min away by foot, runs parallel to the red river and is closed on holidays and Sundays for pedestrian and bike traffic only. You'll also be a 5 min walk to St John's Park, a riverside green space and 4 min drive will take you over to Kildonan Park and Rainbow Stage, an outdoor theatre where you can catch a musical theatre production. Kildonan Park also offers walking trails, and a seasonal pool/waterpark.

Downtown and Exchange District are very easily reached, and only a 7 minute drive away.
